Montgomery County, Maryland got louder last year, more than doubling the amount of reported noise complaints from 2024. 
Last year the county's Department of Environmental Protection recieved 1,058 total complaints. In 2024, that number was just 442.
Complaints are submitted by zipcode, with Potomac's 20854 bringing in 97 noise complaints, the most of any zipcode in 2025. The prior year, the zipcode, which encompasses all of Potomac, only had 19 total submissions.
INTERVIEW WITH COUNTY 311 AGENCY (aka DEP) DIRECTOR JENNIFER MACEDONIA AT PHONE NUMBER 240-777-7781
